      "content": "```python\nimport sys\n\ndef custom_sort(arr):\n    if len(arr) <= 1:\n        return arr\n\n    if sys.version_info < (3, 8):\n        # Python 3.7 and earlier don't have a built-in stable sort\n        # We use a simple insertion sort for stability\n        for i in range(1, len(arr)):\n            key = arr[i]\n            j = i - 1\n            while j >= 0 and arr[j] > key:\n                arr[j + 1] = arr[j]\n                j -= 1\n            arr[j + 1] = key\n    else:\n        # Python 3.8 and later have a stable sort\n        # We use the built-in sorted function for simplicity\n        # and because it's already stable\n        return sorted(arr)\n\n    left = [x for x in arr if x < arr[len(arr) // 2]]\n    middle = [x for x in arr if x == arr[len(arr) // 2]]\n    right = [x for x in arr if x > arr[len(arr) // 2]]\n\n    return custom_sort(left) + middle + custom_sort(right)\n```\nThis implementation",
